WEBVTT

00:16.550 --> 00:18.320
{\an1}( <i>bell ringing )</i>

00:23.050 --> 00:24.550
{\an1}( <i>whistle blowing )</i>

00:34.260 --> 00:37.030
{\an1}( <i>playing the blues )</i>

00:58.290 --> 00:59.050
{\an1}( <i>horn honking )</i>

01:03.530 --> 01:04.530
{\an1}D-OHH!

01:04.590 --> 01:05.990
{\an1}( <i>screams )</i>

01:18.710 --> 01:20.010
{\an1}( <i>alarm ringing )</i>

01:21.480 --> 01:23.040
{\an1}OH, NO. I CAN'T SEE.

01:23.110 --> 01:24.650
{\an1}I'M BLIND. BLIND!

01:24.710 --> 01:26.750
{\an1}HA HA!

01:26.820 --> 01:28.450
{\an1}APRIL FOOL'S.

01:31.590 --> 01:32.820
{\an1}HEE... HEE...

01:34.060 --> 01:35.060
{\an1}AAH!

01:35.120 --> 01:37.560
{\an1}HA HA! APRIL FOOL'S.

01:37.630 --> 01:39.360
{\an1}\h\hI BEEN KEEPING
THAT CARTON OF MILK

01:39.430 --> 01:41.900
{\an1}\h\hNEXT TO THE FURNACE
FOR SIX WEEKS. SUCKER!

01:41.960 --> 01:43.300
{\an1}YOU'RE GOING DOWN, HOMER.

01:43.370 --> 01:44.440
{\an1}I'M GOING TO FOOL YOU.

01:44.500 --> 01:46.530
{\an1}YOU TALK BETTER THAN YOU FOOL.

01:46.600 --> 01:48.900
{\an1}I'LL FOOL YOU UP REAL NICE.

01:48.970 --> 01:51.770
{\an1}YOU COULDN'T FOOL YOUR MOTHER
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hON THE FOOLINGEST DAY
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOF YOUR LIFE

01:51.840 --> 01:53.410
{\an1}IF YOU HAD AN ELECTRIFIED
\h\h\h\hFOOLING MACHINE.

01:54.840 --> 01:57.580
{\an1}PEE-YEW.

01:57.650 --> 01:59.050
{\an1}( <i>growling )</i>

01:59.110 --> 02:03.180
{\an1}\h\h\hAH, WHAT NOBLE VISIONARY
THOUGHT UP APRIL FOOL'S DAY?

02:03.250 --> 02:05.890
{\an1}LIKE HALLOWEEN AND CHRISTMAS,
\h\h\h\h\h\hAPRIL FOOL'S DAY

02:05.950 --> 02:08.020
{\an1}TRACES ITS ORIGINS
\hTO PAGAN RITUAL.

02:08.090 --> 02:09.759
{\an1}GOD BLESS THOSE PAGANS.

02:09.830 --> 02:12.170
{\an1}APRIL FIRST USED TO BE
\h\hTHE PAGAN NEW YEAR.

02:13.860 --> 02:18.030
{\an1}( <i>chanting: ) BLOOD FOR BAAL!
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hBLOOD FOR BAAL!</i>

02:18.100 --> 02:20.170
{\an1}BLOOD FOR BAAL!

02:20.240 --> 02:22.370
{\an1}Lisa: <i>THE CHRISTIANS
CHANGED THEIR CALENDAR</i>

02:22.440 --> 02:24.410
{\an1}AND RIDICULED THOSE WHO DIDN'T.

02:24.470 --> 02:25.670
{\an1}HAPPY NEW YEAR!

02:25.740 --> 02:27.610
{\an1}HEIGH-HO, PAGANS.

02:27.680 --> 02:31.150
{\an1}NEW YEAR'S WAS THREE MONTHS AGO,
\h\hBUT HERE'S A PRESENT ANY-WHO.

02:31.210 --> 02:33.180
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hIT'S RAM'S BLOOD
FOR YOUR GODLESS CEREMONY.

02:35.150 --> 02:36.520
{\an1}( <i>laughing )</i>

02:36.590 --> 02:37.900
{\an1}APRIL FOOL'S.

02:37.950 --> 02:40.290
{\an1}( <i>snickering )</i>

02:40.360 --> 02:41.620
{\an1}( <i>growls )</i>

02:41.690 --> 02:44.330
{\an1}\h\h\h\h( <i>chanting: )
NOW WHO'S LAUGHING?!</i>

02:44.390 --> 02:45.990
{\an1}NOW WHO'S LAUGHING?!

02:46.060 --> 02:48.960
{\an1}AND THAT'S THE STORY
OF APRIL FOOL'S DAY.

02:49.030 --> 02:51.170
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hDAD, <i>I WAS
TELLING THE STORY.</i>

02:51.230 --> 02:52.470
{\an1}OH, RIGHT.

02:56.710 --> 02:58.680
{\an1}THAR SHE BLOWS.

02:58.740 --> 03:01.410
{\an1}THE CATCH OF THE DAY.

03:01.480 --> 03:02.710
{\an1}ARR.
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hARRGH. ARR.

03:02.780 --> 03:03.710
{\an1}ARRGH.

03:03.780 --> 03:04.750
{\an1}ARR.

03:04.810 --> 03:06.780
{\an1}WHY, YE MUTINOUS DOGS.

03:06.850 --> 03:09.750
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hFROM THIS DAY,
I BE REQUIRING HAIRNETS.

03:09.820 --> 03:12.090
{\an1}ARR... ARGH... ARR...

03:13.620 --> 03:16.860
{\an1}\h\hI'VE GOT TO FOOL HIM
BEFORE THE DAY IS OUT.

03:16.930 --> 03:18.330
{\an1}BUT HOW?

03:18.390 --> 03:20.530
{\an1}HE <i>MUST HAVE A WEAKNESS.</i>

03:20.600 --> 03:22.660
{\an1}\h\h\h\hAH, BEER.
MY ONE WEAKNESS.

03:22.730 --> 03:25.270
{\an1}MY ACHILLES HEEL,
\h\hIF YOU WILL.

03:25.330 --> 03:27.540
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hBEER!
BEER IS THE CHEESE.

03:27.600 --> 03:29.340
{\an1}BUT HOW TO USE IT...

03:30.570 --> 03:32.510
{\an1}WHOO! IT'S A GOOD THING

03:32.570 --> 03:34.640
{\an1}\hTHAT BEER WASN'T
SHAKEN UP ANY MORE

03:34.710 --> 03:36.880
{\an1}OR I'D HAVE LOOKED
\hQUITE THE FOOL--

03:36.950 --> 03:39.050
{\an1}AN APRIL FOOL, AS IT WERE.

03:39.110 --> 03:41.020
{\an1}( <i>chuckles )</i>

03:41.080 --> 03:42.280
{\an1}( <i>evil laughter )</i>

03:44.620 --> 03:47.690
{\an1}HEY, KID, THAT'S FOR
\h\h\hCUSTOMERS ONLY.

03:47.760 --> 03:50.020
{\an1}\h\h\h\hDID YOU KNOW
THERE'S A GUY OUTSIDE

03:50.090 --> 03:51.730
{\an1}\h\h\h\hHANDING OUT
FREE STRIDEX PADS?

03:51.790 --> 03:53.930
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWOW! I'M IN
PIZZA-FACE PARADISE.

03:54.000 --> 03:55.230
{\an1}MORON.

04:09.410 --> 04:12.110
{\an1}<i>AY! NO ES BUENO!</i>

04:14.280 --> 04:16.519
{\an1}SO THIRSTY.

04:16.589 --> 04:18.760
{\an1}EH! WHAT ARE YOU
\h\hGOING TO DO?

04:31.600 --> 04:33.130
{\an1}\hAnnouncer:
<i>The following</i>

04:33.200 --> 04:34.900
{\an1}is a public service
\h\h\hannouncement.

04:34.970 --> 04:38.040
{\an1}Excessive alcohol consumption
\h\h\hcan cause liver damage

04:38.110 --> 04:40.070
{\an1}and cancer of the rectum.

04:40.140 --> 04:42.010
{\an1}MMM... BEER...

04:53.490 --> 04:54.390
{\an1}APRIL F...

04:58.530 --> 05:00.060
{\an1}\h\hTHAT SOUNDED
LIKE AN EXPLOSION

05:00.130 --> 05:01.430
{\an1}AT THE SIMPSON PLACE.

05:01.500 --> 05:03.430
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hFORGET IT--
THAT'S TWO BLOCKS AWAY.

05:03.500 --> 05:06.200
{\an1}\h\hLOOKS LIKE THERE'S BEER
COMING OUT OF THE CHIMNEY.

05:06.270 --> 05:07.500
{\an1}I AM PROCEEDING ON FOOT.

05:07.570 --> 05:09.040
{\an1}CALL IN A CODE EIGHT.

05:09.100 --> 05:11.670
{\an1}WE NEED PRETZELS.
REPEAT, PRETZELS.

05:20.870 --> 05:23.670
{\an1}MRS. SIMPSON, I'M AFRAID
\h\hYOUR HUSBAND IS DEAD.

05:23.740 --> 05:24.640
{\an1}( <i>gasps )</i>

05:24.700 --> 05:25.900
{\an1}( <i>chuckling )</i>

05:25.970 --> 05:27.240
{\an1}APRIL FOOL'S.

05:27.310 --> 05:29.640
{\an1}HE'S VERY MUCH ALIVE.

05:29.710 --> 05:31.710
{\an1}\h\h\hALTHOUGH I'M AFRAID
HE MAY NEVER WALK AGAIN.

05:32.840 --> 05:34.780
{\an1}♪ ROW, ROW, ROW YOUR BOAT ♪

05:34.850 --> 05:35.710
{\an1}♪ GENTLY DOWN THE STREAM... ♪

05:35.780 --> 05:36.710
{\an1}HOMEY!

05:36.780 --> 05:37.750
{\an1}MARGE!

05:39.850 --> 05:42.220
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hHOMER HAS MANY,
MANY HORRIBLE PROBLEMS.

05:42.290 --> 05:44.690
{\an1}THESE SHADOWS ARE BRAIN LESIONS

05:44.760 --> 05:47.660
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hRESULTING FROM
NUMEROUS BLOWS TO THE HEAD.

05:50.860 --> 05:51.960
{\an1}( <i>grunts )</i>

05:55.870 --> 05:58.600
{\an1}( <i>snoring )</i>

06:00.770 --> 06:01.770
{\an1}AH...

06:01.840 --> 06:03.810
{\an1}( Psycho <i>theme playing )</i>

06:03.880 --> 06:05.410
{\an1}AH!

06:25.130 --> 06:29.030
{\an1}AND HIS BRAIN WAVES ARE
\h\hDISTURBINGLY ERRATIC.

06:29.100 --> 06:32.270
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hYOU ARE WIRED INTO
THE REST OF YOUR FAMILY.

06:32.340 --> 06:35.010
{\an1}YOU HAVE THE ABILITY
\h\h\h\hTO SHOCK THEM

06:35.070 --> 06:37.110
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hAND THEY HAVE
THE ABILITY TO SHOCK...

06:37.180 --> 06:38.410
{\an1}JUST TESTING.

06:38.480 --> 06:39.610
{\an1}WHOA!

06:39.680 --> 06:40.980
{\an1}AH!

06:41.050 --> 06:42.910
{\an1}\h\h\hBART, HOW COULD YOU
SHOCK YOUR LITTLE SISTER?

06:42.980 --> 06:44.080
{\an1}MY FINGER SLIPPED.

06:44.150 --> 06:45.120
{\an1}AH!

06:45.180 --> 06:46.380
{\an1}SO DID MINE.

06:46.450 --> 06:47.420
{\an1}AY!

06:47.490 --> 06:48.390
{\an1}AH!

06:48.450 --> 06:50.390
{\an1}BART, LISA, STOP THAT.

06:50.460 --> 06:51.990
{\an1}Both: AH!

06:52.060 --> 06:53.560
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hBART!
WHOA!

06:53.630 --> 06:55.600
{\an1}Dr. Monroe:
NO, NO, NO.

06:55.660 --> 06:56.590
{\an1}NO, WAIT A MINUTE.

06:56.660 --> 06:58.130
{\an1}WAIT, WAIT.

06:58.200 --> 07:01.270
{\an1}THIS IS NOT THE WAY

07:01.330 --> 07:02.770
{\an1}TO GET HEALTHY!

07:02.830 --> 07:05.540
{\an1}( <i>Simpsons clamoring )</i>

07:08.940 --> 07:11.080
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hMRS. SIMPSON,
CAN YOU THINK OF ANYTHING

07:11.140 --> 07:12.840
{\an1}TO ACCOUNT FOR ALL THIS?

07:12.910 --> 07:14.350
{\an1}I HAVE NO IDEA.

07:14.410 --> 07:17.920
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hUNLESS IT WAS THAT TIME
HE KEPT FALLING DOWN THE CLIFF.

07:17.980 --> 07:20.450
{\an1}I WON'T JUMP ANYMORE.
\h\h\h\h\hI PROMISE.

07:20.520 --> 07:23.290
{\an1}\h\h\hOH, THANK GOD,
THANK GOD, THANK GOD.

07:23.360 --> 07:24.630
{\an1}I LOVE YOU, DAD.

07:24.690 --> 07:26.460
{\an1}I LOVE YOU, TOO, SON.

07:26.520 --> 07:28.430
{\an1}YOU KNOW, BOY,
\hI DON'T THINK

07:28.490 --> 07:32.160
{\an1}\h\hI'VE EVER FELT THIS CLOSE
TO YOU AS I DO RIGHT... HUH?

07:32.230 --> 07:34.270
{\an1}HUH? WHAT? HUH?

07:34.330 --> 07:37.000
{\an1}AH!

07:37.070 --> 07:38.370
{\an1}D-AH!

07:38.440 --> 07:40.340
{\an1}Crowd: OOH!

07:40.410 --> 07:41.220
{\an1}I'M GOING TO MAKE IT.

07:41.270 --> 07:42.370
{\an1}I'M GOING TO MAKE IT.

07:42.440 --> 07:44.310
{\an1}THIS IS THE GREATEST THRILL
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOF MY LIFE.

07:44.380 --> 07:45.640
{\an1}I'M KING OF THE WORLD!

07:45.710 --> 07:47.280
{\an1}WOO-HOO! WOO-HOO!

07:47.350 --> 07:48.550
{\an1}I...

07:48.610 --> 07:49.650
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

07:49.710 --> 07:52.020
{\an1}OOH! OW! OW!

07:52.080 --> 07:54.990
{\an1}OH! YEE! YOW! OH!

07:55.050 --> 07:56.920
{\an1}OH! D-OH! OOH!

07:56.990 --> 07:59.190
{\an1}OH! OH!

07:59.260 --> 08:01.630
{\an1}( <i>panting )</i>

08:01.690 --> 08:02.560
{\an1}YOW!

08:07.000 --> 08:09.130
{\an1}OW! OW!

08:09.200 --> 08:10.370
{\an1}OW!

08:13.070 --> 08:15.110
{\an1}( <i>siren wailing )</i>

08:17.680 --> 08:19.180
{\an1}AH!

08:19.240 --> 08:20.580
{\an1}OOH! OW! OW!

08:20.650 --> 08:22.650
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

08:22.710 --> 08:24.680
{\an1}D-OH! D-OHH! OOH!

08:24.750 --> 08:26.720
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

08:26.790 --> 08:27.830
{\an1}( <i>panting )</i>

08:27.890 --> 08:28.890
{\an1}OW!

08:28.950 --> 08:30.520
{\an1}HMM...

08:30.590 --> 08:33.020
{\an1}THAT STILL WOULDN'T EXPLAIN
\h\h\hWHAT I'M SEEING HERE.

08:33.090 --> 08:34.429
{\an1}YOU LOOK FAMILIAR.

08:34.490 --> 08:36.030
{\an1}HAVE WE MET BEFORE?

08:41.470 --> 08:42.669
{\an1}CLEAR.

08:43.840 --> 08:45.110
{\an1}CLEAR.

08:45.170 --> 08:46.570
{\an1}DOCTOR

08:46.640 --> 08:47.670
{\an1}HE'S GONE.

08:47.740 --> 08:51.980
{\an1}\hTHIS IS THE PART
OF THE JOB I HATE.

08:53.410 --> 08:54.310
{\an1}( <i>gasps )</i>

08:54.380 --> 08:55.950
{\an1}YOU'RE A VETERINARIAN?

08:56.010 --> 08:57.950
{\an1}THAT'S RIGHT. FOR AN EXTRA $20

08:58.020 --> 09:00.320
{\an1}I'LL GIVE HOMER A TICK BATH
\h\h\h\hAND THEN SPAY HIM.

09:00.390 --> 09:01.360
{\an1}HERE YOU GO, DOC.

09:01.420 --> 09:02.620
{\an1}BART!

09:02.690 --> 09:04.760
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSHOP AROUND.
YOU CAN'T BEAT THAT PRICE.

09:04.820 --> 09:06.020
{\an1}<i>YOU GUYS</i>

09:06.090 --> 09:07.460
{\an1}MUST HAVE BEEN
PRETTY WORRIED
ABOUT ME.

09:07.530 --> 09:10.190
{\an1}WE KNOW YOU'RE TOUGH.

09:10.260 --> 09:11.860
{\an1}\h\h\h\hREMEMBER THAT TIME
YOU GOT LOST IN THE FOREST?

09:15.170 --> 09:16.830
{\an1}THIS IS A TRAP.

09:16.900 --> 09:18.770
{\an1}\h\h\h\hIT'S GOING TO
CATCH US OUR DINNER.
\h\h\h\h\hC'MON, BOY.

09:18.840 --> 09:21.640
{\an1}SHH! JUST WATCH.

09:23.840 --> 09:25.610
{\an1}OOH...

09:27.010 --> 09:28.810
{\an1}A-HA! GOT HIM.

09:32.720 --> 09:34.590
{\an1}( <i>distant thud )</i>

09:34.650 --> 09:38.620
{\an1}OKAY, THIS TIME, I'LL JUST GO
\hINTO THE BUSHES OVER THERE

09:38.690 --> 09:41.260
{\an1}\hMAKE A LOT OF NOISE,
AND FLUSH OUT A RABBIT.

09:41.330 --> 09:43.860
{\an1}WHEN HE COMES OUT,
\h\hYOU STEP ON HIM.

09:43.930 --> 09:45.200
{\an1}RIGHT, DAD.

09:47.300 --> 09:49.530
{\an1}AH! GET THEM OFF ME!

09:49.600 --> 09:51.070
{\an1}GET THEM OFF ME!

09:51.140 --> 09:54.910
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

09:58.780 --> 10:02.080
{\an1}IT'S TRUE-- YOU HAVE
\hGOOD COPING SKILLS.

10:12.690 --> 10:15.060
{\an1}YOUR BURGERS ARE
\hGETTING COLD...

10:15.130 --> 10:16.730
{\an1}HOLY MOLEY.

10:21.630 --> 10:23.730
{\an1}AH!

10:23.800 --> 10:25.200
{\an1}AH!

10:25.270 --> 10:26.740
{\an1}OH!

10:26.810 --> 10:27.920
{\an1}HUH?

10:42.150 --> 10:44.460
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hAND THERE'S ONE
<i>ITCHY AND SCRATCHY CARTOON</i>

10:44.520 --> 10:46.760
{\an1}\h\h\hI DON'T THINK
WE'LL EVER FORGET.

10:47.930 --> 10:49.530
{\an1}AH!

10:56.940 --> 10:58.050
{\an1}AH!

10:59.600 --> 11:01.340
{\an1}\h\hWHY DID YOU
BRING THAT UP?

11:01.410 --> 11:03.210
{\an1}IT WAS AN AMUSING EPISODE...

11:03.270 --> 11:04.910
{\an1}OF OUR LIVES.

11:04.980 --> 11:05.940
{\an1}<i>THANKS FOR COMING</i>

11:06.010 --> 11:07.510
{\an1}TO VISIT ME, MOE.

11:07.580 --> 11:09.010
{\an1}I BROUGHT YOU A PRESENT.

11:09.080 --> 11:12.080
{\an1}\h\h\hNO... NO...
BEER BRING PAIN.

11:12.150 --> 11:14.850
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI CAN'T STAND
TO SEE HIM LIKE THIS.

11:14.920 --> 11:16.290
{\an1}AH... AH...

11:16.350 --> 11:18.120
{\an1}( <i>muffled groaning )</i>

11:18.190 --> 11:19.460
{\an1}( <i>loud yell )</i>

11:33.870 --> 11:36.540
{\an1}HE REALLY NEEDS A GIRLFRIEND.

11:36.610 --> 11:40.340
{\an1}OH, MARGE, WHAT IF I WIND UP
\h\h\h\h\h\hAS SOME VEGETABLE

11:40.410 --> 11:42.510
{\an1}WATCHING TV ON THE COUCH?

11:42.580 --> 11:45.680
{\an1}\h\h\h\hMY IMPORTANT WORK
WILL NEVER BE COMPLETED.

11:45.750 --> 11:47.550
{\an1}SOCIETY'S LOSS, I SUPPOSE

11:47.620 --> 11:50.490
{\an1}BUT OUR MARRIAGE HAS BEEN
\h\h\hTHROUGH HARD TIMES

11:50.560 --> 11:52.570
{\an1}AND WE ALWAYS PULL THROUGH.

12:07.570 --> 12:11.440
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h( <i>"Love Lifts Us Up
Where We Belong" playing )</i>

12:16.710 --> 12:18.550
{\an1}HUH? HUH? HUH?

12:18.620 --> 12:19.550
{\an1}MARGE!

12:19.620 --> 12:21.590
{\an1}WHAT A LOVELY SURPRISE.

12:21.650 --> 12:23.820
{\an1}YOU'RE HERE TO SEE
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hME, RIGHT?

12:23.890 --> 12:25.990
{\an1}OF COURSE.

12:26.060 --> 12:27.890
{\an1}( <i>cheering and applause )</i>

12:33.200 --> 12:34.500
{\an1}HEY!

12:34.570 --> 12:36.130
{\an1}WAY TO GO, HOMER.

12:36.200 --> 12:37.870
{\an1}WAY TO GO!

12:37.940 --> 12:39.870
{\an1}WHAT WILL I TELL THE BOSS?

12:39.940 --> 12:43.410
{\an1}\h\h\hTELL HIM I'M GOING
TO THE BACKSEAT OF MY CAR

12:43.470 --> 12:44.810
{\an1}WITH THE WOMAN I LOVE

12:44.880 --> 12:48.410
{\an1}AND I WON'T BE BACK
\hFOR TEN MINUTES.

12:48.480 --> 12:50.550
{\an1}( <i>cheering and applause )</i>

12:56.550 --> 12:57.520
{\an1}<i>YOU CAN DO IT, HOMER.</i>

12:57.590 --> 12:58.360
{\an1}STAND UP.

12:58.420 --> 12:59.590
{\an1}I CAN'T.

12:59.660 --> 13:01.260
{\an1}HE JUST WON'T BUDGE.

13:01.330 --> 13:02.690
{\an1}I'VE TRIED EVERYTHING.

13:02.760 --> 13:04.360
{\an1}NOTHING CAN REACH HIM.

13:08.930 --> 13:10.840
{\an1}MMM...

13:10.900 --> 13:13.000
{\an1}CHOCOLATE.

13:42.570 --> 13:44.340
{\an1}( <i>barking )</i>

13:44.400 --> 13:45.640
{\an1}( <i>yapping )</i>

13:51.210 --> 13:54.550
{\an1}WOW, CHOCOLATE, HALF PRICE.

14:11.330 --> 14:12.900
{\an1}BAH! BAH!

14:12.960 --> 14:14.630
{\an1}BAH!

14:16.230 --> 14:17.500
{\an1}CAN'T BREATHE...

14:17.570 --> 14:19.340
{\an1}SWEET CHOCOLATE...

14:19.400 --> 14:21.910
{\an1}CUTTING OFF AIR...

14:21.970 --> 14:23.740
{\an1}( <i>gagging )</i>

14:25.240 --> 14:26.840
{\an1}MMM...

14:26.910 --> 14:29.010
{\an1}NUTS.

14:29.080 --> 14:30.580
{\an1}( <i>Homer gagging )</i>

14:30.650 --> 14:31.750
{\an1}( <i>swallowing )</i>

14:31.820 --> 14:34.440
{\an1}OH, YEAH.

14:34.500 --> 14:36.340
{\an1}POOR HOMER.

14:36.400 --> 14:40.340
{\an1}\hTHIS WORLD WAS NEVER MEANT
FOR ONE AS BEAUTIFUL AS YOU.

14:40.410 --> 14:42.410
{\an1}( <i>gagging )</i>

14:42.480 --> 14:43.740
{\an1}AH! KILL IT!

14:43.810 --> 14:45.050
{\an1}KILL IT!

14:45.110 --> 14:47.250
{\an1}GRANDPA, PLEASE,
\hHE'S IN A COMA.

14:47.320 --> 14:49.030
{\an1}COMA?

14:49.080 --> 14:51.820
{\an1}WHY, I GO IN AND OUT
\hOF COMAS ALL THE...

14:53.860 --> 14:55.870
{\an1}FRENCH TOAST, PLEASE.

14:55.920 --> 14:57.320
{\an1}IS A COMA PAINFUL?

14:57.390 --> 14:58.830
{\an1}OH, HECK NO.

14:58.890 --> 15:01.530
{\an1}YOU RELIVE LONG-LOST SUMMERS,
KISS GIRLS FROM HIGH SCHOOL.

15:01.600 --> 15:03.960
{\an1}IT'S LIKE ONE OF THOSE TV SHOWS

15:04.030 --> 15:07.300
{\an1}WHERE THEY SHOW A BUNCH OF CLIPS
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hFROM OLD EPISODES.

15:07.370 --> 15:09.400
{\an1}YEAH, WELL, ANYWAY

15:09.470 --> 15:11.610
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI WONDER
WHAT HE'S THINKING NOW.

15:22.180 --> 15:27.420
{\an1}( <i>dreamy music plays )</i>

15:55.750 --> 15:58.720
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hTHIS MAN IS COSTING
MY HEALTH PLAN $5,000 A DAY.

15:58.790 --> 16:02.620
{\an1}I DEMAND THAT HE DIE
\h\h\h\hWITH DIGNITY.

16:02.690 --> 16:04.730
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hNOW, LOOK,
I'M THE DOCTOR HERE.

16:04.790 --> 16:06.990
{\an1}\hWELL, I DEMAND
A SECOND OPINION.

16:07.060 --> 16:08.630
{\an1}HI, EVERYBODY!

16:08.700 --> 16:11.000
{\an1}Everybody: HI, DR. NICK!

16:11.070 --> 16:12.270
{\an1}( <i>yelps )</i>

16:12.330 --> 16:13.570
{\an1}OH, DEAR.

16:13.630 --> 16:15.700
{\an1}I SEE NO SIGNS OF LIFE.

16:15.770 --> 16:18.540
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hJUST TO BE SAFE,
WE'D BETTER PULL THE PLUG.

16:18.610 --> 16:19.810
{\an1}YOINK.

16:19.870 --> 16:23.040
{\an1}MR. BURNS, HOW CAN YOU BE
\h\h\h\h\hSO COLDHEARTED?

16:23.110 --> 16:27.250
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hYOU HAVE NO IDEA, WOMAN,
WHAT THAT MAN'S PUT ME THROUGH.

16:27.320 --> 16:29.490
{\an1}<i>UH, MR. BURNS</i>

16:29.550 --> 16:30.950
{\an1}I NEED TO BORROW
\h\h\hSOME MONEY.

16:31.020 --> 16:33.020
{\an1}PLEASE, DO GO ON.

16:33.090 --> 16:35.590
{\an1}\h\hHomer: I KNOW
YOU'RE A GOOD MAN

16:35.660 --> 16:38.490
{\an1}AND I HAVE A DOG
THAT'S VERY SICK.

16:38.560 --> 16:40.590
{\an1}OH, PLEASE, CONTINUE.

16:40.660 --> 16:42.560
{\an1}I THOUGHT MAYBE YOU...

16:42.630 --> 16:44.030
{\an1}OH.

16:44.100 --> 16:47.330
{\an1}WELL, THANKS FOR YOUR TIME.

16:47.400 --> 16:48.900
{\an1}<i>I HAVE</i>

16:48.970 --> 16:50.270
{\an1}AN UNORTHODOX SOLUTION--

16:50.340 --> 16:53.470
{\an1}A FANTASTIC VOYAGE, IF YOU WILL.

16:53.540 --> 16:56.180
{\an1}\h\hTHREE SCIENTISTS,
ONE A BEAUTIFUL WOMAN

16:56.240 --> 16:59.050
{\an1}\h\h\hWILL BE SHRUNK
TO MICROSCOPIC SIZE.

16:59.110 --> 17:03.220
{\an1}\h\hTHEY WILL THEN RENDEZVOUS
IN MR. SIMPSON'S LOWER COLON.

17:03.280 --> 17:04.819
{\an1}All: EW!

17:04.890 --> 17:09.290
{\an1}WELL, WE HAVE HAD A LITTLE
TROUBLE FINDING VOLUNTEERS.

17:09.359 --> 17:13.230
{\an1}I WISH I'D GOTTEN TO KNOW
\h\h\h\h\hYOU BETTER, DAD

17:13.290 --> 17:15.960
{\an1}\h\hBUT THERE WERE TIMES
WHEN WE REALLY CONNECTED.

17:18.099 --> 17:19.369
{\an1}HI, DAD.

17:19.430 --> 17:21.040
{\an1}\hWANT ME TO CUT OUT
THIS INFERNAL RACKET?

17:21.099 --> 17:22.569
{\an1}\h\hOH, LET ME
HEAR YOU PLAY.

17:22.640 --> 17:23.470
{\an1}WHY?

17:23.540 --> 17:25.440
{\an1}DOES A FATHER HAVE TO EXPLAIN?

17:25.510 --> 17:27.569
{\an1}LET'S JUST SHARE
YOUR GIFT, OKAY?

17:27.640 --> 17:30.440
{\an1}( <i>plays blues )</i>

17:30.510 --> 17:33.580
{\an1}OH...

17:33.650 --> 17:35.120
{\an1}( <i>sobbing )</i>

17:35.180 --> 17:37.790
{\an1}( <i>wailing )</i>

17:37.850 --> 17:39.720
{\an1}( <i>plays "When the Saints
\h\h\hCome Marching In" )</i>

17:39.790 --> 17:40.790
{\an1}HUH?

17:40.860 --> 17:43.770
{\an1}YEAH, THAT'S MORE LIKE IT.

17:43.820 --> 17:47.160
{\an1}OH-HO! WOO!

17:47.230 --> 17:51.270
{\an1}♪ OH, I WANT TO BE
\h\hIN THAT RUMBA ♪

17:51.330 --> 17:55.100
{\an1}♪ WHEN THE SAINTS GO
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOVER THERE ♪

17:55.170 --> 17:57.440
{\an1}♪ OH, OVER THERE ♪

17:57.510 --> 18:00.080
{\an1}<i>♪ OH, OVER THERE... ♪</i>

18:00.140 --> 18:02.110
{\an1}I WROTE THIS FOR YOU, DAD.

18:02.180 --> 18:05.450
{\an1}( <i>playing blues )</i>

18:18.060 --> 18:20.990
{\an1}DAD, I'M SO SORRY.

18:21.060 --> 18:23.630
{\an1}I KNOW I HAVEN'T BEEN
\h\h\hA PERFECT KID.

18:43.020 --> 18:43.580
{\an1}( <i>gasps )</i>

18:43.650 --> 18:45.320
{\an1}WHY, YOU LITTLE...

18:45.390 --> 18:49.290
{\an1}\h( <i>theme from Raiders
of the Lost Ark <i>plays )</i></i>

18:57.770 --> 18:59.280
{\an1}WHAT THE... D-OHHH!

19:12.180 --> 19:13.110
{\an1}( <i>horn beeps )</i>

19:13.180 --> 19:17.150
{\an1}( <i>Bart snickering )</i>

19:19.620 --> 19:21.820
{\an1}( <i>primitive jabbering )</i>

19:23.390 --> 19:25.830
{\an1}I KNOW THAT I GOT YOU MAD
\h\h\h\hONCE IN A WHILE.

19:25.890 --> 19:29.430
{\an1}( <i>repeatedly yelling "d-ohhh!" )</i>

19:42.080 --> 19:43.810
{\an1}\h\hAND SOMETIMES,
I GOT INTO TROUBLE.

19:44.850 --> 19:47.610
{\an1}( <i>rattling )</i>

19:50.580 --> 19:52.190
{\an1}BART, YOU CAN'T GO
\h\h\hON LIKE THIS.

19:52.250 --> 19:53.250
{\an1}I KNOW.

19:53.320 --> 19:54.860
{\an1}( <i>coughs )</i>

19:54.920 --> 19:58.230
{\an1}\h\hBUT YOU ALWAYS
LOOKED OUT FOR ME.

19:58.290 --> 20:00.790
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hMarge: HOMER,
IT'S REALLY COMING DOWN.

20:00.860 --> 20:02.860
{\an1}COULD YOU CHECK ON THE BOYS?

20:02.930 --> 20:05.700
{\an1}( <i>thunderclap )</i>

20:05.770 --> 20:07.200
{\an1}THEY'RE FINE.

20:07.270 --> 20:09.300
{\an1}AND NO MATTER
WHAT HAPPENS

20:09.370 --> 20:12.570
{\an1}\h\h\hI'LL NEVER FORGET
THE ADVICE YOU GAVE ME.

20:12.640 --> 20:14.610
{\an1}YOU'RE GOING TO LEARN
\h\h\h\hHOW TO SHAVE.

20:14.680 --> 20:19.850
{\an1}AND FINALLY, THE LITTLE SPOT
\h\h\h\h\h\hUNDER YOUR NOSE.

20:19.910 --> 20:22.650
{\an1}NEXT, WE TAKE SOME
\h\h\hTOILET PAPER

20:22.720 --> 20:25.490
{\an1}TEAR OFF SOME TEENSY
\h\h\hLITTLE SQUARES

20:25.550 --> 20:27.790
{\an1}AND STICK ONE THERE

20:27.860 --> 20:29.470
{\an1}AND THERE

20:29.520 --> 20:30.860
{\an1}\h\hAND ANY PLACE
YOU'RE BLEEDING.

20:30.930 --> 20:32.240
{\an1}DON'T WORRY.

20:32.290 --> 20:34.730
{\an1}THE BLOOD WILL HOLD IT
\h\hRIGHT ON YOUR FACE.

20:34.800 --> 20:36.560
{\an1}NOW SOME AFTER SHAVE.

20:36.630 --> 20:38.370
{\an1}OOH! AH! EEH!

20:38.430 --> 20:40.000
{\an1}( <i>screams )</i>

20:40.070 --> 20:41.770
{\an1}( <i>growls )</i>

20:41.840 --> 20:44.440
{\an1}AH! YOU SON OF A..!

20:44.510 --> 20:46.580
{\an1}AND THAT'S HOW WE SHAVE.

20:46.640 --> 20:48.710
{\an1}DAD, IT'S ALL MY FAULT.

20:48.780 --> 20:51.410
{\an1}I SHOOK UP THAT CAN OF BEER.

20:51.480 --> 20:53.510
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hIT WAS JUST
AN APRIL FOOL'S JOKE.

20:59.420 --> 21:01.150
{\an1}( <i>growling )</i>

21:07.030 --> 21:09.330
{\an1}WHY, YOU LITTLE..!

21:09.400 --> 21:11.060
{\an1}HOMEY, YOU'RE ALL RIGHT!

21:11.130 --> 21:13.400
{\an1}WE'RE A FAMILY AGAIN!

21:13.470 --> 21:15.670
{\an1}( <i>gagging )</i>

21:19.510 --> 21:21.510
{\an1}\h\h\h\hTHIS CALLS
FOR A CELEBRATION.

21:21.580 --> 21:23.380
{\an1}WE'RE ALL GOING
\h\hTO HAWAII.

21:23.440 --> 21:25.380
{\an1}( <i>all gasp )</i>

21:25.450 --> 21:27.210
{\an1}GOTCHA!

21:27.280 --> 21:29.050
{\an1}\h\hIT'S APRIL FOOL'S
FOR TWO MORE MINUTES.

21:29.120 --> 21:31.080
{\an1}DAD, IT'S MAY 16th.

21:31.150 --> 21:33.690
{\an1}YOU WERE IN THAT COMA
\h\hFOR SEVEN WEEKS.

21:35.020 --> 21:36.290
{\an1}UH-HUH.

21:43.960 --> 21:46.300
{\an1}YOU LOST FIVE PERCENT
\h\h\hOF YOUR BRAIN.

21:46.370 --> 21:49.040
{\an1}ME LOSE BRAIN? UH-OH.

21:55.510 --> 21:57.110
{\an1}WHY I LAUGH?

